-- Government Malpractice, Abuse of Power Cases Increase 6%, China Daily Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-28T00:07:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/government-malpractice-abuse-of-power-cases-increase-6-china-daily-says.html
Chinese prosecutors handled 6
percent more cases of malpractice and abuse of power by civil
servants from November 2009 to August 2010 as compared to the
same period a year earlier, the China Daily reported today,
citing Cao Jianming, prosecutor-general of China’s Supreme
People’s Procuratorate.  A total of 298 officials at or above the county level were
investigated during the period, an 8 percent increase from a
year earlier, according to the Beijing-based newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
